From 02aa2769631956bfec51bbd32367ea3c01eb22bf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ripan Deuri <rdeuri@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 9 Jun 2025 15:16:57 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:DP:wifi:ath12k: Fix MSI issue for Pebble with hybrid
 bus

On hybrid bus platform, MSI data isn't populated in dp_msi_data, before DP SRNG setup,
leading to incorrect interrupt mapping for DP SRNGs. Resolve this by initializing MSI
before setting up DP SRNGs.

Signed-off-by: Ripan Deuri <rdeuri@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp.c
index 3c70811..cdb4326 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp.c
@@ -1905,11 +1905,11 @@ int ath12k_dp_cmn_device_init(struct ath12k_dp *dp)
 {
 	int ret;
 
-	ret = ath12k_dp_setup(dp->ab);
+	ret = ath12k_dp_arch_op_device_init(dp);
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;
 
-	ret = ath12k_dp_arch_op_device_init(dp);
+	ret = ath12k_dp_setup(dp->ab);
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;
 
-- 
2.34.1

